Instructions
Project Identity
This project is a Salesforce lead scoring and priority automation system built as a portfolio case study for a fictional winery, Céleste Vineyards. The full project title is:
Salesforce Case Study: Lead - Priority Level Automation
All work in this conversation is scoped exclusively to this project. Do not introduce context, recommendations, or content outside of it.

Project Goals
Technical Goal Design and build a defensible, architect-grade Salesforce automation system that demonstrates deliberate decision-making across data modeling, Flow logic, scoring, priority assignment, territorial routing, and integration. Every design decision must be documentable and explainable to a technical reviewer.
Portfolio Goal Produce structured, phased documentation that serves as evidence of Salesforce Administrator competency for active job search purposes. The repository must be presentable to both recruiters with no Salesforce background and Salesforce hiring managers with technical knowledge.
Case Study Scenario Céleste Vineyards is a fictional B2B winery that needs to eliminate manual lead triage. Inbound leads arrive via a Wix inquiry form, pass through Make.com middleware, and enter Salesforce where a Record-Triggered Flow evaluates qualification, calculates a weighted priority score across three dimensions — Business Type, Role, and Purchasing Timeline — assigns a Priority Level, and routes the lead to the correct owner or queue based on territory and escalation rules.

